					<description><![CDATA[<p>Crypto savings accounts are increasingly used as a way to earn passive income in 2026. Bank rates barely beat inflation. Many crypto holders look for ways to generate yield from</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/crypto-savings-accounts-in-2026-comparing-rates-and-features/" data-wpel-link="internal">Crypto Savings Accounts in 2026: Comparing Rates and Features </a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Crypto savings accounts are increasingly used as a way to earn passive income in 2026. Bank rates barely beat inflation. Many crypto holders look for ways to generate yield from idle assets. Variable APYs create problems because they change fast. A rate of 12 percent today can drop to just 3 percent next month.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fixed-income products work differently. You lock in the rate from the start and receive payments in stablecoins. </span><a href="https://varntix.com/?utm_source=ventureburn&amp;utm_medium=list2304&amp;utm_campaign=news" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Varntix</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> offers a fixed-rate model with advertised returns of up to 24% APY in USDT or USDC.  Varntix is a digital platform that provides fixed-return crypto savings products.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The sections below compare Coinbase, Nexo, Binance Earn, and Ledn with this model. </span></p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-200340 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/prvb2542025ft1-1.png" alt="Crypto Savings Accounts" width="512" height="287" /></p>
<h2><b>How major savings accounts compare</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Listed below are the platforms reviewed in this guide:</span></p>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><b>Platform</b></td>
<td><b>Supported Assets</b></td>
<td><b>APY</b></td>
<td><b>Payout Currency</b></td>
<td><b>Lockup Period</b></td>
<td><b>Fees</b></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Coinbase</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">USDC, ETH, SOL</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Up to 4.5%</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Asset held</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">None</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Withdrawal fees</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Nexo</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">120+ including BTC, ETH</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Up to 14%</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Asset or NEXO</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Flexible or fixed</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">None</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Binance Earn</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">100+</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">2% to 8%</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Asset held</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Flexible or locked</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Varies</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ledn</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">BTC, USDC, USDT</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Up to 8.5%</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Asset held</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Flexible</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">None</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Varntix</span></td>
<td><b>Diversified crypto</b></td>
<td><b>Up to 24%</b></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">USDT / USDC</span></td>
<td><b>6, 12, or 24 months</b></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">None</span></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h2><b>Crypto Savings Platforms Overview </b></h2>
<h3><b>1. Coinbase: simple USDC rewards with low yields</b></h3>
<p><b>Rating: 8.9/10</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Coinbase pays around 4.1% APY on USDC balances automatically, with monthly payouts and no lock-ups. Rates climb to 4.5% for Coinbase One subscribers.</span></p>
<p><b>Pros of Coinbase savings</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Regulated US public company</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">No lock-up on USDC rewards</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Automatic enrollment for eligible accounts</span></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Cons of Coinbase savings</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Only 4.1% to 4.5% on USDC</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Limited asset selection</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Withdrawal fees eat small balances</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><b>2. Nexo: high-yield tiered savings</b></h3>
<p><b>Rating: 8.5/10</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Nexo advertises rates of up to 12–14% APY on stablecoins and BTC, with daily compounding and flexible withdrawals. Top rates require holding NEXO tokens and picking fixed terms.</span></p>
<p><b>Pros of Nexo savings</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Daily interest compounding</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Flexible and fixed-term options</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">120+ supported assets</span></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Cons of Nexo savings</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Top rates need NEXO token holdings</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Variable yields change often</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Custodial, not on-chain</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><b>3. Binance Earn: broad product suite with mid-range rates</b></h3>
<p><b>Rating: 8.6/10</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Binance Earn bundles Simple Earn, Dual Investment, and locked products across 100+ assets. Flexible stablecoin deposits pay 2% to 3%, while locked terms reach 8%.</span></p>
<p><b>Pros of Binance Earn savings</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Widest asset coverage</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Flexible and locked options</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Deep liquidity and reliable payouts</span></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Cons of Binance Earn savings</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Flexible stablecoin rates only 2% to 3%</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Yields shift with promotional periods</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Complex menu of products</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><b>4. Ledn: conservative Bitcoin and stablecoin Growth Accounts</b></h3>
<p><b>Rating: 8.7/10</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ledn offers Growth Accounts for BTC, USDC, and USDT with rates up to 8.5% on USDT. Monthly payouts, proof-of-reserves audits, and a narrow product set.</span></p>
<p><b>Pros of Ledn savings</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Up to 8.5% on USDT</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Monthly proof-of-reserves reports</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Regulated Canadian firm</span></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Cons of Ledn savings</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Limited asset selection</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rates change with market demand</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Availability varies by country</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><b>5. Varntix: fixed-rate stablecoin income</b></h3>
<p><b>Rating: 9.6/10</b></p>
<p><a href="https://varntix.com/?utm_source=ventureburn&amp;utm_medium=list2304&amp;utm_campaign=news" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Varntix</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> uses a fixed-rate model that differs from variable-rate platforms. Users select a rate at the beginning, which remains fixed for the selected term. Payouts are made in USDT or USDC. Fixed-term products advertise returns of up to 19.7% APY, with a minimum deposit of $500, with 6, 12 or 24 month lock up periods. The flexible savings account offers rates between 4% and 6.5%  and opens from just $50.</span></p>
<p><b>Pros of Varntix</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rates are fixed from the start of the term </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Payments are made in USDT or USDC </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Early withdrawals are described as having no penalties </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Payouts are available on a weekly, monthly, or quarterly basis </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Smart contracts are reviewed by independent firms </span></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Cons of Varntix</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rates can differ from one funding round to the next</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">You get no bonus if crypto prices climb sharply</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The better yields ask for a 6-to-24-month commitment</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><b>How the Varntix Model Works </b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Users begin by creating an account on Varntix. Funds can be deposited using crypto or card payments  and choose either the fixed-term note or the flexible savings account. The selected rate remains fixed for the duration of the term once you confirm it. Stablecoin payments reach you weekly, monthly, or quarterly depending on the schedule you select. Early withdrawals are stated to be available without penalties. </span></p>
<h2><b>Conclusion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Variable crypto savings rates may offer higher initial returns. In some cases, these rates may decrease over time. Users seeking fixed returns may consider platforms that offer fixed-rate products such as Varntix. The platform provides fixed rates, stablecoin payouts, and predefined terms. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Varntix is a digital wealth platform focused on fixed income in crypto and on-chain convertible notes. Learn more at </span><a href="https://varntix.com/?utm_source=ventureburn&amp;utm_medium=list2304&amp;utm_campaign=news" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400;">varntix.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<h2><b>Frequently Asked Questions</b></h2>
<h3><b>Why do savings rates on Coinbase, Nexo, and Binance change so often?</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Most platforms use variable rates that depend on market demand and promotions. A good rate today can drop sharply next month, so your actual monthly income ends up lower than expected.</span></p>
<h3><b>How easy is it to get your money out on Varntix?</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The flexible savings account lets you withdraw anytime with no penalties. Even the fixed-term notes allow early redemption without extra charges if your plans change.</span></p>
<h3><b>What is the smallest amount needed to start on Varntix?</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can open the flexible savings account with just $50. Fixed-term notes start at $500. This may make it more accessible for beginners to start using the platform. </span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/crypto-savings-accounts-in-2026-comparing-rates-and-features/" data-wpel-link="internal">Crypto Savings Accounts in 2026: Comparing Rates and Features </a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
